description: Grande Armee Investissement SA, (also G.A.I., formerly EFE Edition Formation Entreprise), is a France-based holding company specialized in legal publishing, training activities and consulting. The Company's activities are organized around two branches: Grande Armee Conseil and EFE. Grande Armee Conseil offers consulting services in the fields of fiscal affairs for the research sector, innovation financing, local tax matters, administrative management of professional risks, and social charges. EFE provides training services in a wide range of subjects, including banking and finance, insurance, asset management, accounting, fiscal affairs, corporate law, social law, urban planning, public services, environment and energy, marketing and communication, purchasing and international strategy; EFE also specializes in the publishing of legal books and periodicals.

Maison Antoine Baud SA engages in real estate investment. The company is headquartered in Cournon D Auvergne, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 5 full-time employees. The firm owns and manages corporate real estate assets such as offices, warehouses and business premises, mainly in the region of Auvergne. The main shareholder of the Company is Cogeval - Societe pour le Conseil et la Gestion de Valeurs Mobilieres.

Myomo, Inc. is a United States-based medical device company specializing in myoelectric orthotics for people with neurological disorders. The Company’s products help to restore function in individuals with neuromuscular conditions, such as brachial plexus injury, spinal cord injury, multiple sclerosis and stroke. Its MyoPro myoelectric limb orthosis is a powered brace that supports a weakened and deformed arm for functional use. The MyoPro is an elbow/wrist/Hand orthosis, which supports the arm and helps to bend and straighten the arm at the elbow. The brace provides assistive function for joint motion that enables a user to self-initiate and control movements of a partially paralyzed arm using their own muscle signals. When the user tries to bend their arm, sensors in the brace detect the weak muscle signal, which activates the motor to amplify their weak muscle signal to help bend and move their arm. The brace uses non-invasive skin sensors.

Parfex SA is a France-based company active in the perfume industry. description: Mexco Energy Corp. operates as an independent oil and gas company, which engages in the acquisition, exploration, development, and production of natural gas properties and crude oil. Made engages in the development, marketing and maintenance of detection and measurement equipment and software for the energy, building and public works, shipbuilding, armament, and telecommunications markets. Novatech Industries SA also offers services related to the construction of prototype electronic cards and their analysis. The products are provided to household electrical appliance, telecom, medical, energy, electronics and optical telecom sectors.

WEACCESS GROUP SA operates as a telecommunication service provider. The company is headquartered in St-Etienne-Du-Rouvray, Normandie and currently employs 11 full-time employees. The company provides the Internet access, telecommunications infrastructure and hosting services, as well as Voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP) telephony solutions and others. The firm delivers its services in the areas which are not facilitated with the asymmetric digital subscriber line (ADSL). The company also offers necessary equipment, such as antennas, routers, cables, Ethernet power modules and universal serial bus (USB) connectors, among others. The firm operates in several French regions, including Alpes de Hautes Provence, Indre, Manche, Seine et Marne and Meuse, among others.

Batla Minerals engages in the research, exploration, and operation of diamond mines. The company is headquartered in Cres, Occitanie and currently employs 199 full-time employees. The firm has diamond operations in Lesotho, and is specialized in the research, exploration and operation of diamond mines. The Company’s clients include De Beers and Gem Diamonds. The firm has prospecting rights for a tungsten/molybdenum/rare earths deposit in South Africa. The Company’s operations are managed by El Nino Mining (Pty) Ltd, South Africa.

Onlineformapro SA engages in the design and development of online training solutions. The company is headquartered in Vesoul, Bourgogne-Franche-Comte. The firm's expertise is structured around three main areas of e-learning training: Technology, Contents and Services. Technology segment provides training platforms, collaborative work and Web conference platforms. Content segment provides interactive and instructed training modules in the areas of office skills, Web design, CAD/CAM, management, accounting and languages, among others. Services segment offers consulting services, remote tutoring services, training for designers and instructors, training assessment and educational content presentation, setting up tutoring programs, transfer of technical skills and content hosting and other services. The Company’s customers include Societe Generale, Banque Populaire, Canal Plus, Faurecia, Total, APRR, Alcatel-Lucent, Cora, Carrefour and Alstom, among others.

Dynafond SA engages in the manufacturing and marketing of light alloy parts. The company is headquartered in Etrepagny, Normandie and currently employs 44 full-time employees. The company manufactures alloy parts from both aluminum and zamak (a mixture of zinc, aluminum, magnesium and copper) in the process of gravity and high-pressure die casting. The firm's products are used in various industrial sectors, including motor vehicle, cycles and motorcycles, farm machinery, electrical and heating appliances, as well as light fittings and aeronautics. Dynafond SA is a part of the Alufond Group, which holds an 83% stake in the Company.

MonFinancier SA, formerly Allo Finance SA, is a France-based company active in the financial sector. It provides consulting services in the area of financial investments. The Company’s business is divided into five segments: Media, providing economic information; Assets and Investments, providing investment solutions and insurance savings; Exchange, providing stock solutions for securities accounts; Taxation; providing tax income advisory; and Estate, offering programs for real estate rental.

Franck Deville SA is a France-based company, which specializes in developing and manufacturing craftsman tradition cocktail products to high range hotel and catering professionals and gourmet products selective distribution specialists. The company provides sweet and salty sweet mini macaroons, and sweet and salty sweet mini puffs.

Troc de l'ile SA engages in consignment sale of second-hand household, leisure, and sporting goods. The company is headquartered in Les Angles, Pays De La Loire and currently employs 110 full-time employees. The company displays and sells second-hand goods, such as furniture, decorations, electrical goods, do-it-yourself items, leisure, child welfare products, audio, video, culture and multimedia items to consumers on behalf of the owner. The firm operates through over 170 sales points and a number of franchise stores in France, Belgium, Luxembourg, Spain, Germany and Switzerland. The company is also involved in renting out commercial buildings. The firm offers online purchasing and selling services via its Website: www.troc.com. The firm operates through a number of subsidiaries and affiliated companies, including Trocmag SAS, Troc SAS, Iberia, SCI les Lauzes, SCI Canaux, SCI Faisses, SCI Woippy and SCI Dole Trade, among others. The firm is controlled by Troc Europe SAS.

Umalis Group SA is a France-based company active in the field of information technology (IT) and telecommunications. The Company specializes in wage portage in the computing and engineering fields. The group supports experts wishing to develop a secure professional activity independently enjoying the benefits of employee status. Umalis Group is organized in network around a computing platform intended to simplify and rationalize the management of the wage portage of the consultants.

Hopening SA, formerly Optimus SA, is a France-based company engaged in the development of marketing campaigns designed for charity associations, public interest groups and ethical businesses. The Company promotes general interest projects, develops public awareness, and facilitates the collection of funds. The Company’s activities include three main lines: Fundraising, including consulting, direct and online marketing and event organization, among others; Communication, which includes strategic consulting, brand and communication strategy and Database Services, including data analysis, data mining, data collection and management, through a software package Qualidata, which enables the data collection from different sources. Its clients include schools and universities, laboratories and healthcare institutes, environmental, handicapped and humanitarian associations, among others. It merged with Excel.

Easson Holdings Limited, formerly Easson Telecom Limited, is a Hong Kong based investment holding company principally engaged in the climate change and energy transformation business. The Company is involved in carbon trading, reducing emissions from deforestation and forest degradation (REDD+), green finance, and biomass supply chain management. Green finance business provides financial advisories for environment and clean energy projects, as well as company financing. Biomass supply chain management business provides biomass supply chain management services for biomass power plants, biomass heating plants and biomass steam boilers. The Company is also engaged in environment and energy infrastructure, consultation and construction business.

Mulann SA is a France-based company, which manufactures and distributes magnetic stripes for cards and smartcards. Its product and service portfolio includes plastic cards and smartcards, paper cards and tickets, production machines, test tool machines, expertise and training, as well as maintenance and technical support..

Infoclip SA engages in the provision of information management and hosting services for small and medium enterprises. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France. The company is engaged in every stage of the preliminary study assistance benefits allowing users to work in conditions of comfort and maximum efficiencies. The firm is active in various areas of expertise, such as network engineering, implementing management solutions (in the fields of accounting and finance, management of purchases, sales and stock, payroll and Human Resources, production manageent and management of customer relationships), application development, training people, support and maintenance and outsourcing. Its products portfolio include specialezed in the field of management solutions Sage (such as Sage Line 100, Sage Line 1000, Sage CRM, among others) and SAP.

Visio Nerf engages in the design, manufacture, and marketing of industrial viewing machines. The company is headquartered in Vezins, Pays De La Loire and currently employs 17 full-time employees. The firm designs and builds modular image processing systems dedicated to camera controls, including automatons and associated software. The company designs its products for the automobile, food processing, electronics, aerospace and armament, as well as for packaging sectors, among others. The firm's client portfolio included British American Tobacco, Chocolats Van Dyck, Cuisine de France, Elbi, Renault, Volkswagen, Philips, Bosch, Caterpillar and Fleury Michon, Haubis, Comptoir de la confiserie, Delpierre, Delta Composants, Deville, Direction Generale de l’Armement (DGA), Delice de la Tour, Carnaud Metalbox, among others.

As SA is a France-based company, which operates in the banking industry. The Company provides its services through a number of sites, including www.rapidopret.fr , www.rapido-artisans.com, www.rapido-immo.com and www.rapido-assur.fr. The Company operates into four main sectors: Funding, which provides a range of services regarding interest rates, loan repurchase and renegotiation; Real Estate, which connects individuals with real estate professionals, including real estate agencies, notary agencies and agents of transactions, among others; Works, allows the connection between private individuals and craftsmen, and Insurance which offers 100% dematerialized approach between clients and individual partners.

Air Marine SA is a France-based company, which operates as an air operator. The Company uses aircraft and drones in line with the technical and financial expectations of its customers. The Company covers a wide spectrum of air missions. Including Topography, Which is made from aerial photos or ‘’LIDAR’’ captures; Linear monitoring, which includes the monitoring of linear networks such as pipelines, railways or electric, rivers and borders; Structure inspection, which includes inspections of punctual structures such as dams, water, towers, wind turbines and factories, among others, and solar panel inspection, which includes research of hot spots on electrical installation and thermal balances from captures by drones or planes. In addition, the Company also provides services such as zone surveillance, target towing missions and plastering missions.

Damaris SA is a France-based designer and distributor of information storage software for companies. The Company specializes in the provision of solutions for archiving and managing documents in a secure way, such as supplier and client invoices, pay slips and accounting lists. It also designs products directed at specific sectors, such as software for archiving check details for banks, for archiving receipts and delivery notes for lorry drivers and for archiving hospital invoices. The Company provides solutions for the banking, industry, health care, public, service and logistics sectors. The Company’s services include Damaris Archives, Damaris Global Solution, Damaris Transports, Damaris Cash Processing, Damaris Tracabilite Credit, Damaris Dossier Patient Unique and Damaris Alert Mail, among others. In September 2013, the Company announced that it has acquired 100% of the shares in Scan Concept SAS, a company which specializes in digital security for documents.

France Tourisme Immobilier SA is an investment holding company with interest in real estate assets ownership and management sector. The company is headquartered in Araches, Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes and currently employs 34 full-time employees. The Company’s jewelry collection is based around gemstones and pearls, and its products include watches with interchangeable straps; hearts to be fitted on rings, earrings, pendants and bracelets; and the Symbole ring, which consists of two gold bands that are set around a central, flat axis, revealing an engraved message or a line of diamonds. Poiray Joaillier SA retails its products via its Parisian stores and has a stand in the Galeries Lafayette department store in Paris. In addition to that, the Company has a store located in Tokyo and also retails its products via a network of retailers in Belgium, Ireland, Morocco, Spain, Japan, France and Luxembourg. In April 2014, FIPP SA acquired 50,62% of the Company.

Body One Lingerie SA is a France-based company that specializes in the marketing of a range of lingerie for women. The Company’s activities revolve around three product families, including lingerie articles, such as bras, panties, undershirts, strapless bras and others; nightwear, comprising nightdresses, pyjamas, dressing gowns and others, and swimwear, including swimming costumes and sarongs, among others. Body One Lingerie SA distributes its products through a network of branch offices, franchise points, affiliates and subsidiaries.

Phone Web SA engages in telesales. The company is headquartered in Paris, Ile-De-France and currently employs 93 full-time employees. The firm specializes in the outsourcing of call centers to provide services such as telemarketing, telesales, telephone surveys and satisfaction polls, call reception services, including after-sales services and order taking, and the training of telephone marketing staff. The firm operates two production sites, in Paris and Amiens, France.

Sumo Resources PLC is a France-based company principally engaged in the minerals trading and extraction. The Company focuses on Tantalum and Niobium, which is used in the manufacture of mobile electronics, specialized medical equipment and steel alloys like those used in the manufacture of airplane engines, among others. The Company has strategy of creating small scale mining projects and trading houses in identified areas by providing subsidiaries for each project in each country. It establishes mining industry in the frontier regions. The Company operates in the United Kingdom, Hong Kong, France, Germany and Democratic Republic of the Congo, among others. In addition to the minerals sources through the trading houses, the Company develops properties with surface and opencast mining techniques.

Imalliance SA is a France-based company engaged in the digital imagery. It provides a range of services, from initial consultancy to actual usage, including the creation of databases. The Company’s activities are divided into four main areas: consulting and project management; image processing, including digital photography and Internet service provision (ISP); engineering, largely consisting of digital imagery, and project work, such as online marketing, Internet imagery and an Internet portal to financial information. The Company's customers consist of advertisers, communication agencies and press publishers. Images are created for food, accessories, decor, furniture, packaging, textile, fashion and automobile industries. Some of the customers include, Carrefour, BUT, Nuni, Mr Bricolage, DIOR, Garnier, Publicis, LVMH, Petit Fute, Editions Lito and Aeroport Nantes Atlantique, among others.

Gour Medical SA is a pharmaceutical company, whiche engages in the research, development, and commercialization of medicines and food supplements for animals. The company is headquartered in Zug, Zug. Its portfolio includes a number of products, which includes the Gour 153 pain and improvement of quality of life product and the Gour 419 atopic dermatitis project. The Gour 153 product offers an approach, especially for the long-term management of pain thanks to a new formula based on Cannibidiol.

A Toute Vitesse SA (ATV) is a France-based company engaged in the provision of courier services. The Company transports various sizes of letters and parcels for small and medium-sized companies. ATV offers four types of services: the delivery of letters and parcels in Paris or Ile-de-France, via couriers on motorbikes, in cars or lorries; the provision of regular pick-ups and deliveries on pre-determined days and hours; the provision of specific distribution operations; and national and international messaging services. The Company has a fleet of 125 motorcycles, 102 cars and six trucks and it is also engaged in renting of its vehicles. It operates two wholly-owned subsidiaries, TZF SAS and Facilicar SNC.

Energie Europe Service SA engages in the production of decentralized renewable energy. The company is headquartered in Courbevoie, Ile-De-France. Its activity is organized into three areas: production of photovoltaic solar energy, development of plants for producing thermal and electric power from agricultural and forest biomass, and processing into energy of biogases from waste and byproduct gases from methanization. As of the end of 2011, the Company had 20 energy production plants located in France.

Everset SA is a French company that is primarily engaged in the distribution and retail of motorcycles and boats. The Company offers a wide range of motorcycles, scooters and quads under brands such as Kawasaki, Triumph, Ktm, Derbi and Sym. It also offers a large choice of leisure crafts, fishing boats, inflatable boats and jet skis under brands such as Everset, Wellcraft, Larson and Sea-doo. Everset SA sells new, as well as second hand products. In addition, the Company sells clothes, such as isothermal suits, shoes, gloves, vests, glasses and helmets, and accessories, including rinse-down tools, batteries, bilge pumps, tanks and mooring systems, among others.

description: Azorean Aquatic Technologies SA is a Portugal-based company primarily engaged in the manufacture of consumer electronics. Through the app, user moves the drone, as well as takes pictures and videos by an embedded camera, which sends images to smartphone via wireless (Wi-Fi) connection. Furthermore, Ziphius allows real-time video camera streaming and setting the vertical angle of the lens, as well as playing augmented reality (AR) games. The drone enables to explore salt and sweet underwater environment.

Mld SA, formerly known as Arthur Maury SA, is a France-based company primarily engaged in the field of stamp-collecting and numismatics. The Company specializes in the distribution and sale of stamps, medals, numismatic coins and tickets in France and abroad. It also publishes its own philatelic catalogues.

The Company also holds a participation in Harley-Davidson Shop Sarl, which commercializes a range of goods under the Harley-Davidson brand name, as well as under its own brand, Buell, in Levallois Motos and in Immobiliere Standard SCI.

description: AZ Leasing SpA is an Italy-based company involved in the provision of leasing services. The Company is also active in the leasing of equities; real estate properties, such as warehouses, industrial buildings, laboratories, commercial building, offices, malls and hotels, and trademarks and patents.

Colipays Reunion SA, formerly known as Colipays Reunion SAS is a France-based company specialized in mail-order and e-commerce. It operates in three sectors: Commercial, including sale of gifts by various means (direct sales, by fax, by mail, by Internet); Industrial, which combines parcels in assembly line, and Logistics, which covers the sale of fresh and perishable products and shipping them to the final customers. The Company offers a range of gift hampers containing Reunion’s products, such as tropical flowers, exotics fruits and Creole savours. In Addition, Colipays Reunion SA offers to its clients a loyalty program, which allows them to accumulate points. The company also delivers parcels to the customers by Chronopost International.

Consort NT SA is a French company primarily engaged in the design, development and implementation of information technology (IT) architectures and solutions for companies. The Company has three main areas of expertise: engineering services, through which it provides design, operation and maintenance of scientific, industrial and other professional solutions; infrastructure services, which includes consulting, system integration and IT management services in the fields of network and telecommunications and IT systems; and application services, which also include consulting, system integration and IT management services for financial, generic and technological applications. The Company's subsidiaries include Consort Technologie, Consort Sarl, Consort Netcom, Consort Devline, CMS and Consort Mediterranee. The Company primarily works with large companies in the industrial, service, banking, finance and insurance sectors.

Corep Lighting SA designs, manufactures, and sells lampshades and decorative lighting fixtures. The company is headquartered in Begles, Nouvelle-Aquitaine and currently employs 277 full-time employees. The firm produces a range of styles, such as contemporary, decorative and classical, which are sold to furniture stores, department stores, do-it-yourself shops and lighting shops, among others. The company’s product range includes: lampshades, table lamps, ceiling lights, wall lights, standard lamps and spotlights. The firm operates through its subsidiaries, such as Corep SAS, Market Set SAS, Forestier SARL, Goodlight LTD, Corep Iberica SUL, Corep Lighting India Pvt Ltd, ADM LightSAS and Koralcoa SA.
Courbet SA, formerly Societe Anonyme Courbet, is a France-based company engaged in investments in industrial and commercial undertakings and asset management.

EAVS Groupe manufactures products such as interface items, including distributors, matrices, adapters, media players and electronic power converters, among others; cords for video, audio, cinema, and software equipment; audio products like microphones, headsets and loud speaker enclosures, among others; connectors; video and display items like CCTV, projectors and screens; cables for audio, video and remote controls; accessories and supports and security items like cameras and recorders. It markets the products through brand names Acer, AOC, APC, BTX, Camelion, Carlon, Gefen and Leviton, among others. The Company has sales offices located in Paris, Cannes, Rhone-Alpes and the Southwest region.

The Company invests in solar power plants and is engaged in the planning, structuring, financing and sale of projects. The Company's regional focus is on Italy, Germany, France and India.

Eduniversal SA, formerly SMBG SA, is a France-based company specializing in training and careers guidance. The Company offers advice on university and professional qualifications, and provides support and training services to help candidates to be successful in their application forms. Eduniversal SA’s services are aimed at both undergraduate and postgraduate students, as well as professionals, universities and corporate clients. The Company manages several Websites, including www.smbg.fr, which offers search tools and online information for undergraduate students, www.master1.fr, which is aimed at the graduate students with the Bachelor degree and www.eduniversal.com, which proposes the selection of business schools among others. The Company also publishes guides on professional trainings, the French university system and Masters Degrees. It has one subsidiary SMBG Finances Sarl.

Metalliance engages in the designing, manufacturing, and marketing of public works machine and equipment. The company is headquartered in St-Vallier, Bourgogne-Franche-Comte and currently employs 117 full-time employees. The Company’s main products include equipment for control and scanning vehicles, public works construction equipment intended for underground works and road construction; vibratory handling equipment; industrial equipment, including machinery and plants for finishing, handling and addition, as well as components and welded sub-assemblies made of various metals, such as steel and aluminum. The firm has one subsidiary, Traingle Service Industrie SARL. As of December 31, 2011, the Company was 50%-owned by Sofico and 43%-owned by Gaussin.

Finaxo Environnement SA is a France-based company specializing in the design and fabrication of the equipment for water treatment and conditioning. The Company's activity is organized around four product families: lamellar decantation systems, used in decanting raw surface water, domestic and industrial waste water, rain water and in hydrocarbon separation; water treatment equipment, such as ultra-filtration units for surface, underground, saline, and soft water; biogas valorization and lixiviate treatment equipment, including flare stacks, subsurface containment centers, sensors, biogas burners, evaporators; and treatment units for organic materials by pyrogasification: elimination of wastes, such as plastics, sludge, tires, wood and automobile remnants by thermal decomposition.

Galeo Concept SA is a France-based company that specializes in designing and selling scented products and interior decorating items. The company’s products include scented products, such as scented candles, chafing dish candles, potpourri, incense, scented oils and scent tablets, among others; decorating products such as wrought iron and glass candle holders, incense holders, oil diffusers, perfume vaporizers and vases and wellbeing products, including soaps and essential oils, among others.

Groupe Carnivor engages in the distribution of meat and dairy products. The company is headquartered in Toulon, Paca and currently employs 847 full-time employees. The Company’s product range includes various kinds of fresh meat and other meat products, such as cooked meats and sausages, as well as ready-to-eat products. The other products include, cheese, cremeries and pasta products, among others. The company distributes its products to the wholesalers and through a network of 36 sale points situated in seven French regions: Alpes-Maritime, Var, Bouches-du-Rhone, Gard, Isere, Herault and Vaucluse. The firm is also involved in real estate activities like purchase and sale land, buildings and commercial centers, among others. As of December 31, 2012, the Company operates through subsidiaries, including Saprimex, Carnivor SARL, Chapelette SCI, Paca immo, Emilcost sarl, among others.

Les Maisons d Aujourd Hui SA is a France-based company engaged in the construction and marketing of individual houses.
